{"id": 225042506, "title": "Jaishanker, Nirmala, Vaishnaw, Dr Jitendra Among Modi&#8217;s Most Highly Educated Ministers", "text": "NEW DELHI, May 29: The Modi government has a diverse and highly educated cabinet, with ministers possessing impressive academic credentials from prestigious institutions worldwide. Here is a closer look at the educational backgrounds of some of the most highly educated ministers. Follow the Daily Excelsior channel on WhatsApp Dr. Subrahmanyam Jaishankar Designation: Minister of External Affairs Dr. Subrahmanyam Jaishankar is a distinguished diplomat with an extensive academic background. He holds a degree from St. Stephen\u2019s College, University of Delhi. He further pursued a Master\u2019s in Political Science, an M.Phil, and a Ph.D. in International Relations from Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU), Delhi. His diplomatic career includes assignments in embassies in Moscow, Colombo, Budapest, and Tokyo, as well as key positions within the Ministry of External Affairs and the President\u2019s Secretariat. Nirmala Sitharaman Designation: Minister of Finance & Minister of Corporate Affairs Nirmala Sitharaman has a strong foundation in Economics. She earned her undergraduate degree in Economics from Seethaiakshmi Ramaswamy College in Tiruchirapalli. She then pursued her Master\u2019s degree in Economics at Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU), New Delhi. Professionally, she has served as an assistant to the Economist at the Agricultural Engineers Association in London and later as Senior Manager (Research and Analysis) with Price Waterhouse, also in London. Ashwini Vaishnaw Designation: Minister of Railways, Minister of Communications & Minister of Electronics and Information Technology Ashwini Vaishnaw has a robust technical and administrative background. In 1991, he graduated with a gold medal in electronic and communications engineering from MBM Engineering College (JNVU), Jodhpur. He secured an all-India rank of 27 in the Indian Administrative Service (IAS) examination in 1994. Later, in 2008, he pursued an MBA at the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania, USA. Dr. Jitendra Singh Designation: Minister of Science and Technology Dr. Jitendra Singh has an extensive medical and scientific background. He completed his M.B.B.S. and M.D. in Medicine, and holds a Fellowship in Diabetes & MNAMS in Diabetes and Endocrinology. He has received education from Stanley Medical College in Chennai, All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS) in New Delhi, Government Medical College in Jammu, and an Honorary Ph.D. from Amity University. Dr Jitendra Singh was Professor of Medicine for more than 25 years and his pioneering research works in \u2018Diabetes in Pregnancy\u2019 and \u2018Stress Diabetes in Migrants\u2019 received wide recognition. He still continues to be the Life Patron of the largest academic organisation of Diabetologists, the RSSDI (Research Society for Study of Diabetes in India). Piyush Goyal Designation: Minister of Commerce and Industry, Minister of Consumer Affairs, Food and Public Distribution & Minister of Textiles Piyush Goyal is well-versed in commerce and law. In 1984, he completed his Bachelor of Commerce (B.Com) degree at H.R. College of Commerce & Economics, University of Mumbai. He earned a Bachelor of Laws (LL.B) degree from Government Law College, University of Mumbai in 1987, and in the same year, he also qualified as a Chartered Accountant from the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI). Jyotiraditya M. Scindia Designation: Minister of Civil Aviation & Minister of Steel Jyotiraditya Scindia has an impressive educational pedigree. He started his higher education at St. Stephen\u2019s College, University of Delhi, before transferring to Harvard College, where he earned a Bachelor of Arts in Economics in 1993. He further pursued a Master of Business Administration degree from Stanford Graduate School of Business in 2001. General (Retd.) V.K. Singh Designation: 